ctors/Principals and other stakeholders to be prepared for the resumption exercise. It could be recalled that the students of JSS-1 and SS-1 were directd to stay at home for five weeks. Vanguard News Nigeria Kano State Government says it will fumigate 528 public and private schools to make it safe for students writing their West African Examination Council (WAEC) in the state. August 3, 2020 In "News" Kano State Government says it will fumigate 528 public and private schools to make it safe for students writing their West African Examination Council (WAEC) in the state. The government also fixed August 10 for the reopening of schools for the exit students in the state. The Commissioner for Education,… August 4, 2020 In "News" Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu of Lagos State has said Churches and Mosques to can begin to hold full services, while private and public primary schools are to reopen on Monday, September 21. September 19, 2020 In "News"